The G-7 leaders express their concern over Russia's actions in Ukraine, including the illegal annexation of Crimea and destabilization of eastern Ukraine. They condemn the downing of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 and call for a prompt and transparent international investigation. The leaders demand a ceasefire at the crash site to allow investigators to do their work and recover the remains of the victims. They urge Russia to stop supporting separatist groups and participate in creating the necessary conditions for a political solution. The G-7 leaders announce additional sanctions on Russia and emphasize the need for a peaceful settlement of the crisis in Ukraine. They call on Russia to use its influence with the separatists and ensure effective border control. If Russia does not de-escalate the situation, the leaders are prepared to further intensify sanctions.